# Goal Description

The goal is to create a modern, premium login page with an exceptional UI/UX. The design will feature a sleek dark mode with subtle glassmorphism effects, a smooth gradient background in deep blues and purples, and dynamic micro-animations to make the interface feel alive and responsive. 

Here is a mockup of the proposed design direction:

![Login Page Mockup](C:\Users\Lenovo\.gemini\antigravity\brain\d2274d69-2069-41d5-8091-14aa58bac81d\login_page_mockup_1776409631051.png)

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> Please review the mockup image above. Let me know if you like this design direction or if you prefer a different color palette (e.g., light mode, different accent colors).

## Open Questions

> [!NOTE]
> 1. **Framework:** I plan to build this using **Vite + Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS** for maximum performance and flexibility, without relying on external UI libraries. Let me know if you prefer a specific framework like React or Vue.
> 2. **Authentication:** Currently, this will just be the UI frontend. Do you want to add any basic mock validation logic in JavaScript (e.g., checking if email is valid)?

## Proposed Changes

We will create a new web project in the workspace with the following structure:

### Project Setup
- Use `npx create-vite` to scaffold a Vanilla JavaScript project.

### Core Files

#### [NEW] `index.html`
- Contains the semantic HTML structure for the login form.
- Includes email input, password input (with a toggle visibility button), "Forgot Password" link, "Sign In" button, and Social Login buttons.

#### [NEW] `style.css`
- Contains the premium Vanilla CSS styling.
- Implements CSS variables for easy theme changes.
- Uses glassmorphism (backdrop-filter) for the form container.
- Adds smooth hover effects and focus states for all interactive elements.

#### [NEW] `main.js`
- Adds interactivity such as the password visibility toggle and basic input animations.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Run the local development server (`npm run dev`).
- Open the application in the browser.
- Verify that the UI matches the high-end aesthetic of the mockup.
- Test hover effects, focus states, and the password toggle functionality to ensure a smooth user experience.
